I manually triggered both automations as visible Codex threads on the remote Linux `scope-vcs` project:

::created-thread{threadId="019f18fc-d72e-7270-bdf1-3ba95379a176"}

::created-thread{threadId="019f18fc-e733-7671-82bc-c573f2278e96"}

Both threads are active. The first is updating Linear completed projects, and the second is auditing `scope-vcs`. The transferred automation TOMLs are still present under `/home/adam-blumoff/.codex/automations`, but I did not leave a Linux systemd schedule in place because that would create hidden background runs, which is not what you want.

